961
01:11:41,702 --> 01:11:44,078
I think that if I were working
beside a woman all day long,

962
01:11:44,163 --> 01:11:46,873
I could appreciate
her abilities and intellect

963
01:11:46,957 --> 01:11:48,624
without taking her to bed.

964
01:11:50,294 --> 01:11:51,669
I'm sorry, have we met?

965
01:11:52,296 --> 01:11:54,380
I don't recall.
But let's assume we haven't.

966
01:11:54,465 --> 01:11:56,132
Helen Stewart, Hugh Alexander.

967
01:11:56,216 --> 01:11:58,092
So who do you agree with?
Alan or myself?

968
01:11:58,177 --> 01:11:59,802
Well, Alan, of course.

969
01:12:00,637 --> 01:12:02,930
I'm very flattered really, but I...
I don't think that...

970
01:12:03,015 --> 01:12:04,557
Rubbish.

971
01:12:04,641 --> 01:12:06,934
Well, I work beside a man every day

972
01:12:07,019 --> 01:12:09,270
and I can't help but have developed
a bit of a crush on him.

973
01:12:09,354 --> 01:12:11,230
Well, who is this man?
So I can kick his arse.

974
01:12:11,315 --> 01:12:13,232
Oh, there's no need to worry,
it's been chaste.

975
01:12:13,317 --> 01:12:16,235
We've never even met. He's a German.

976
01:12:16,320 --> 01:12:18,446
Now I really want to kill him.

977
01:12:18,530 --> 01:12:22,325
Er... How... How do you mean
you work alongside a German?

978
01:12:23,035 --> 01:12:26,454
Well, each of us intercepts messages
from a specific German radio tower.

979
01:12:26,538 --> 01:12:28,039
So we have a counterpart
on the other side

980
01:12:28,165 --> 01:12:29,582
who's tip-tapping out the messages.

981
01:12:29,666 --> 01:12:31,334
Everyone types a touch differently,

982
01:12:31,418 --> 01:12:33,544
so you get to know
the rhythm of your counterpart.

983
01:12:33,670 --> 01:12:35,421
