984
01:12:35,506 --> 01:12:37,381
I feel as if I know him so well.

985
01:12:37,508 --> 01:12:38,800
It's a pity he has a girlfriend

986
01:12:38,884 --> 01:12:41,427
but that's why I disagree
with you, Mr Alexander,

987
01:12:41,595 --> 01:12:43,429
because I'm in love
with a co-worker of sorts

988
01:12:43,514 --> 01:12:44,931
and we've never even met.

989
01:12:45,390 --> 01:12:48,101
Well, allow me to buy you another pint
and I'll tell you why you're wrong.

990
01:12:48,852 --> 01:12:50,228
Let's.

991
01:12:50,687 --> 01:12:52,313
Excellent.

992
01:12:54,691 --> 01:12:56,234
Thanks.

993
01:12:56,693 --> 01:13:00,238
Erm... Pints and a sloe gin.

994
01:13:03,367 --> 01:13:05,660
In case you were wondering,
that's what flirting looks like.

995
01:13:05,744 --> 01:13:07,203
Helen!

996
01:13:08,539 --> 01:13:10,581
- Alan!
- Yes, Alan?

997
01:13:11,125 --> 01:13:14,335
Why do you think your German
counterpart has a girlfriend?

998
01:13:14,419 --> 01:13:15,920
It's just a stupid joke.
Don't worry about it.

999
01:13:16,046 --> 01:13:17,547
No, no, no, no, no. Tell me.

1000
01:13:19,049 --> 01:13:21,259
Well, each of his messages
begins with the same five letters.

1001
01:13:21,385 --> 01:13:23,427
C-I-L-L-Y.

1002
01:13:23,887 --> 01:13:26,222
So I suspect that Cilly
must be the name of his amore.

1003
01:13:26,306 --> 01:13:28,432
But that's impossible.
The Germans are instructed to use

1004
01:13:28,559 --> 01:13:30,601
five random letters
at the start of every message.

1005
01:13:30,727 --> 01:13:32,311
Well, this bloke doesn't.

1006
01:13:32,813 --> 01:13:34,981
Love will make a man
do strange things, I suppose.

1007
01:13:35,566 --> 01:13:37,150
In this case,

1008
01:13:37,234 --> 01:13:39,110
love just lost Germany
the whole bloody war!

1009
01:13:39,945 --> 01:13:41,821
- Oh!
- Go, Peter.

1010
01:13:43,740 --> 01:13:45,116
Sorry.

1011
01:13:46,910 --> 01:13:48,828
Alan!

1012
01:13:48,912 --> 01:13:51,581
Alan!

1013
01:13:51,665 --> 01:13:53,666
- Whoa, whoa!
- Stop!

1014
01:13:55,252 --> 01:13:56,919
- No, no, no...
- Stop! Stop! Stop! Stop!

1015
01:13:58,589 --> 01:14:01,841
Hugh Alexander. John Cairncross.
Peter bloody Hilton.

1016
01:14:02,092 --> 01:14:03,843
Alan?

1017
01:14:04,011 --> 01:14:05,469
What...

1018
01:14:08,140 --> 01:14:10,433
What... What if...

1019
01:14:10,517 --> 01:14:14,937
What if Christopher doesn't have to
search through all of the settings?

1020
01:14:15,147 --> 01:14:17,523
What if he only has to search through

1021
01:14:17,608 --> 01:14:21,027
ones that produce words we already
know will be in the message?

1022
01:14:21,111 --> 01:14:23,946
- Repeated words. Predictable words.
- Exactly.

1023
01:14:26,783 --> 01:14:28,367
Look. Look, like this one.

1024
01:14:28,452 --> 01:14:30,953
"0600 hours. Weather today is clear.
Rain in the evening.

1025
01:14:31,038 --> 01:14:32,455
"Heil Hitler."

1026
01:14:34,124 --> 01:14:35,625
Oh, that's it.

1027
01:14:35,751 --> 01:14:37,126
Exactly.

1028
01:14:37,252 --> 01:14:40,463
They send a weather report
every day at 6:00 a.m.

1029
01:14:41,048 --> 01:14:42,798
So that's... That's three words we...

1030
01:14:42,883 --> 01:14:45,134
we know will be
in every 6:00 a.m. message.

1031
01:14:45,219 --> 01:14:47,887
Er, "weather", obviously and...

1032
01:14:47,971 --> 01:14:50,306
- Heil bloody Hitler?
- Heil bloody Hitler!

1033
01:14:51,767 --> 01:14:53,434
Here's the 6:00 message
from this morning.

1034
01:15:00,817 --> 01:15:03,486
Hugh, the, er, the right-hand
letter wheels. Set them to...

1035
01:15:03,570 --> 01:15:04,987
Yes, yes, I know.
"Weather" and "Hitler".

1036
01:15:05,072 --> 01:15:06,489
- Peter, John.
- Yes.

1037
01:15:06,573 --> 01:15:08,908
Run voltages through those letters,
through the back scramblers.

1038
01:15:08,992 --> 01:15:10,493
- So we'll use the loops?
- Yes.

1039
01:15:10,619 --> 01:15:12,662
Joan, what was the last
6:00 a.m. message?

1040
01:15:12,746 --> 01:15:14,330
- L.
- L.

1041
01:15:15,749 --> 01:15:17,166
- H.
- H.

1042
01:15:17,751 --> 01:15:19,752
- W.
- W.

1043
01:15:19,836 --> 01:15:21,587
- A.
- A.

1044
01:15:22,089 --> 01:15:23,506
Q.

1045
01:15:25,926 --> 01:15:27,343
Done.

1046
01:15:44,695 --> 01:15:47,029
Come on. Come on, Christopher.

1047
01:16:03,672 --> 01:16:05,047
Oh, my God.

1048
01:16:12,055 --> 01:16:13,556
What... What happened?

1049
01:16:15,642 --> 01:16:17,310
- Did it work?
- Alan?

1050
01:16:17,394 --> 01:16:19,437
Alan! Alan!

1051
01:16:22,482 --> 01:16:23,899
I need a new message.

1052
01:16:23,984 --> 01:16:25,401
The latest intercept.

1053
01:16:29,656 --> 01:16:31,073
Thanks.

1054
01:16:32,159 --> 01:16:33,868
E...

1055
01:16:35,162 --> 01:16:37,079
O... T.

1056
01:16:37,164 --> 01:16:38,331
- Ready?
- Yes.

1057
01:16:38,415 --> 01:16:39,415
- M.
- M.

1058
01:16:39,541 --> 01:16:40,583
- Y.
- Y.

1059
